{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Knowledge that a friend or relative is using drugs can cause significant psychological stress to a caring or sensitive individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegally acquired date rape drugs could be even more dangerous to victims, as they may be cut with dangerous chemicals. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Many drug users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugs-brains-behavior-science-addiction/drug-misuse-addiction) do not consider the negative repercussions of drug use and are convinced they can easily control their use. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education and information campaigns could be funded by taxes on the drugs themselves. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Science can already study drugs, just with some [constraints](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4307971/). I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, the potency of available alcoholic drinks grew significantly \\([pg. 3](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Benzodiazepines are [readily available](http://w-bad.org/statistics/) in most countries for common complaints like insomnia, jet lag and performance anxiety, and are actually more effective at increasing the effects of alcohol than barbiturates.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Specialists working for the government could provide the necessary education on the subject of responsible substance use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Addictions can lead to improper care of children, relatives, or any person \\(even animals\\) who depends on the user.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[New research](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/0269881118806297) on PTSD has shown that MDMA-assisted psychotherapy is an extremely effective treatment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}
